The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: The government is giving final touches to a new income tax code, which will soon be put in the public domain. The new income tax code will make it easier for tax payers and professionals to understand the tax rules. The codes are almost ready and they will be out soon, a finance ministry official said.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: The government will bring changes in the insurance act, finance minister P. Chidambaram said after a meeting on insurance with a group of ministers. We will go to the cabinet now, he said but refused to give details of the decisions taken.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 1: Wind turbine maker Suzlon Energy has signed an agreement with Portugal-based Martifer for the acquisition of the latters entire stake in REpower Systems for 270 million euros.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 1: Vadodara-based 20 Microns Ltd will be the first company to come out with an initial public offering under the new Sebi guidelines of applications supported by blocked amount.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: Sugar mills in Uttar Pradesh will have to pay farmers an extra Rs 1,480 crore by September 6. The Supreme Court refused to stay the Allahabad High Court judgment to pay the state-advised price of Rs 125-130 per quintal for the 2007-08 season.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: Uco Bank will finalise a foreign partner for its proposed financial services subsidiary           
	d of this month.The bank has also received the approval of the Reserve Bank of India to open 102 branches in the current financial year.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 1: Trade timings on the Bombay Stock Exchange would change from September 24 to October 8 as VSAT services might get disrupted during this period because of heavy solar activity.                                                                                                                         
